    {
      "id": "1521796270635880492",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-01T08:35:04.527+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "But TBH I'm not sure how common it is to harden various block independently. That prevents optimization at boundary and also cost area since macro are rectangular and blocks often harden more into blob shapes.",
      "author": {
        "id": "596068704471482370",
        "name": "246tnt",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "tnt",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2026-07_media/88d17af9d19ab43565b0c46751ef7d12-DFEE5.png"
      },
      "attachments": [],
      "embeds": [],
      "stickers": [],
      "reactions": [],
      "mentions": [],
      "inlineEmojis": []
    },
    {
      "id": "1521796509765730345",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-01T08:36:01.54+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "The only case where I see blocks hardened as macro are highly optimized ones where there was significant manual/scripted/layout/... work to make it a separate block. Something like a SRAM / memory or something like that.",
      "author": {
        "id": "596068704471482370",
        "name": "246tnt",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "tnt",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
